Rules:<br>
1. The Hunt has begun, it ends Sunday at 8pm pst.<br>
2. To help clear banks and slots, items may be checked<br>
between 5pm and 6pm each day of the hunt at the location below, send a tell to Tyre or one of the treasurers saying you are ready.<br>
3. The following treasurers will be available:<br>
   Quartermaster - Neriak Bank<br>
   Rassalon      - Kadalim City Entrance/Butcherblock<br>
   Krikor        - Halas<br>
   Balthezar     - South Freeport Gate<br>
   Mimir         - GF Wizard Spires<br>
4. Items marked with a ** become property of the Court of Ruins and will be held in trust for it's members.<br>
5. Yes, I know that most of you can just go out and purchase these things, that takes all the fun out of it.<br>
6. Don't try to figure out why some things are worth more than others, you never will, it was done using PFA style.<br>
7. There are now many many prizes, we will not even be giving them all out in just this event. Those that are not given out will go back into the guild treasury and WE WILL see to it that they go into the specific class tresauries asap (ie bonechips will be given to the necro treasury. I would suggest selling them to the necro treasury, but I fail to understand why a guild needs hard plat on the books)<br>
8. If you are one of the &quot;first&quot; people to complete certain itmes, please announce it on guild so your accomplishment is acknowledged (ie RTS, golden stud earrings etc)<br>
9. Note: it is possible that there may be additional items thrown in from time to time without any warning, you may want to check here and see (NAH I would never do that....&lt;evil grin&gt;<br>
